<details class="admin-howto">
  <summary class="admin-howto__summary">How to assign students to an internship placement</summary>
  <div class="admin-howto__body">
    <p class="admin-howto__lead"><strong>Three ways (use whichever fits your workflow):</strong></p>
    <ol class="admin-howto__list">
      <li><strong>Internships → Select students &amp; assign</strong> — Pick a placement, search or filter applicants, tick rows, then <em>Assign selected students</em>. Good for batch work.</li>
      <li><strong>Each placement → Students (roster)</strong> — Open a placement, use <em>Add students</em> with the same search, filters, and bulk actions.</li>
      <li><strong>Applications → open an applicant</strong> — Use the <em>Internship placement</em> dropdown on their profile and <em>Save placement</em>.</li>
    </ol>
    <p class="admin-howto__note">Assigning someone who is already on another placement <strong>moves</strong> them to the new one. <strong>Inactive</strong> placements cannot receive new assignments until you activate them under Edit.</p>
  </div>
</details>
